{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Delay the Plug-in Car grant cut",
        "additional_details": "The Government announced on 18 March a cut to the Electric Car Grant from \u00a33,000 to \u00a32,500, with immediate effect and no warning.\r\n\r\nUK car dealerships have been closed during the COVID-19 lockdown making car purchases difficult. Therefore, many customers have been forced to delay purchases until lockdown is eased and make a safe purchase.\r\n\r\nThe immediate cut to the plug-in car grant DURING lockdown is poorly timed and offered no fair warning to customers waiting to make a purchase.",
        "background": "Delay the reduction to the plugin car grant until lockdown is eased and car purchases can be completed. Since car dealerships closed during lockdown, customers have been unable to purchase a vehicle. The timing of the grant cut is unfair and poorly timed.",
